WEBVTT

00:01.702 --> 00:04.036
Marcie:
<i> The last couple of years</i>
<i> have been tough, right?</i>

00:04.038 --> 00:05.437
<i> Challenging.</i>

00:06.573 --> 00:07.439
<i> We've had to fight</i>
<i> for the little things</i>

00:07.475 --> 00:09.775
<i> That make us feel human.</i>

00:10.945 --> 00:13.111
<i> We've had to get used</i>
<i> to a life in stasis.</i>

00:14.081 --> 00:15.314
<i> Praying that you</i>
<i> get to finish</i>

00:15.449 --> 00:18.216
<i>Whatever you were in the middle</i>
<i> of when the world changed.</i>

00:20.187 --> 00:21.653
<i> Don't get me wrong,</i>

00:21.722 --> 00:24.656
<i> Life in the midst of a</i>
<i> pandemic wasn't all bad.</i>

00:25.192 --> 00:26.458
Cheers.

00:26.593 --> 00:27.826
Cheers.

00:29.296 --> 00:31.696
Marcie:
<i> We were reminded of how</i>
<i> much we love our loved ones.</i>

00:33.234 --> 00:36.334
<i> We "bubbled" with strangers</i>
<i> and made lifelong friends.</i>

00:36.370 --> 00:37.736
Hey, hold on!

00:37.738 --> 00:39.805
Marcie:
<i> And while most of us</i>
<i> were dealing with a virus</i>

00:39.874 --> 00:44.576
<i>That made being socially distant</i>
<i>from loved ones the new normal,</i>

00:44.612 --> 00:48.814
<i> Some of us saw our lives</i>
<i> irrevocably changed by loss.</i>

00:50.084 --> 00:51.283
(colleen sighs)

00:51.352 --> 00:54.286
Marcie:
<i> Every morning, my client,</i>
<i> nina francis,</i>

00:54.288 --> 00:56.688
<i> Would make the journey</i>
<i> from preston to halifax</i>

00:56.690 --> 00:58.823
<i> To work as a</i>
<i> continuing care assistant</i>

00:58.859 --> 01:02.461
<i> At one of oakland park's</i>
<i> long term care facilities.</i>

01:02.530 --> 01:06.298
<i> And she did that job</i>
<i> efficiently, diligently</i>

01:06.367 --> 01:08.100
<i> And with the</i>
<i> greatest of care.</i>

01:08.235 --> 01:09.434
<i> During the pandemic,</i>

01:09.437 --> 01:11.103
<i> She was required</i>
<i> to do this job</i>

01:11.238 --> 01:14.306
<i> Under the</i>
<i> worst circumstances.</i>

01:14.375 --> 01:16.040
<i> Lack of ppe,</i>

01:16.077 --> 01:18.710
<i> No access to n-95 masks,</i>

01:18.712 --> 01:20.378
<i> Being shuttled across</i>
<i> oakland park's</i>

01:20.414 --> 01:22.714
<i> Six long term</i>
<i> care facilities.</i>

01:24.284 --> 01:26.918
<i> My client is charged with</i>
<i> assault with a weapon</i>

01:26.954 --> 01:28.720
<i> And criminal negligence.</i>

01:28.756 --> 01:31.589
<i> She's not guilty,</i>
<i> ladies and gentlemen.</i>

01:31.625 --> 01:36.528
Nina francis was confronted
by the complainant at her home,

01:36.663 --> 01:39.564
As she was taking her two
young children to school.

01:39.633 --> 01:42.300
<i> Now the complainant</i>
<i> attacked my client</i>

01:42.302 --> 01:45.170
<i> Because she believed</i>
<i> that ms. Francis</i>

01:45.172 --> 01:47.673
Gave her mother covid-19;

01:47.808 --> 01:50.075
A virus she did succumb to.

01:50.144 --> 01:51.943
<i> My client attempted</i>
<i> to escape</i>

01:51.979 --> 01:54.546
<i> Ms. Macaskill's</i>
<i> unrelenting attack.</i>

01:54.681 --> 01:56.181
<i> And when ms. Eilidh macaskill</i>

01:56.316 --> 02:00.952
Refused to back away
from my client's vehicle,

02:00.988 --> 02:02.354
She was injured.

02:03.824 --> 02:06.958
<i> The crown is gonna tell you</i>
<i> this accident was purposeful.</i>

02:07.928 --> 02:10.496
<i> This case is an</i>
<i> unwarranted attack</i>

02:10.631 --> 02:15.400
<i> On a woman who risked</i>
<i> her own life every day</i>

02:15.536 --> 02:18.503
Through one of the most
unprecedented events

02:18.506 --> 02:19.904
Of our lifetime.

02:20.875 --> 02:22.774
<i> Ladies and gentlemen</i>
<i> of the jury,</i>

02:22.776 --> 02:27.579
<i> Covid-19 has taken so</i>
<i> much from so many people.</i>

02:29.650 --> 02:32.450
Don't allow it to claim
nina francis' freedom

02:32.486 --> 02:33.785
And her family too.

02:34.822 --> 02:36.621
Please find her
not guilty.

02:37.191 --> 02:38.623
Thank you.

02:41.328 --> 02:42.527
Judge kilcoyne:
<i> Call your first witness.</i>

02:42.530 --> 02:43.862
Yes your honour.

02:43.864 --> 02:45.463
We call
eilidh macaskill

02:45.499 --> 02:46.831
To the witness stand.

02:48.869 --> 02:54.740
(ominous music)

