03:19.667 --> 03:20.899
Driver:
(laughing)<i> I cannot</i>
<i>believe what I have-</i>

03:20.901 --> 03:22.100
Passenger:
<i>Is she all right?</i>

03:22.169 --> 03:23.435
<i>Keep filming,</i>
<i>I'm gonna call 911.</i>

03:23.504 --> 03:24.836
Driver:
<i>All right. Oh my-</i>

03:24.838 --> 03:26.170
<i>Are you okay?</i>

03:29.410 --> 03:30.709
Ms. Macaskill,

03:30.711 --> 03:32.844
There's no doubt
that video must be
triggering for you.

03:32.846 --> 03:33.779
<i>Do you need a moment?</i>

03:33.914 --> 03:34.846
I'm good.

03:34.882 --> 03:35.814
Bethany:
<i>Okay.</i>

03:35.949 --> 03:38.717
Now, can you tell the
court what happened

03:38.786 --> 03:42.320
After the accused's
truck made
contact with you?

03:42.389 --> 03:45.123
I'm not sure,
I just remember
being in a lot of pain.

03:45.125 --> 03:48.026
Do you recall if
the accused stopped

03:48.062 --> 03:49.361
To see if you
were okay?

03:49.964 --> 03:51.029
She just ran off.

03:51.065 --> 03:51.997
Bethany:
<i> She just left the scene?</i>

03:52.066 --> 03:53.064
Eilidh:
<i> Yes.</i>

03:53.133 --> 03:55.133
And she didn't
come to your aid?

03:55.135 --> 03:56.969
No. She ran
inside her house.

03:57.104 --> 03:59.137
<i>Two guys came from</i>
<i>I don't know where</i>

03:59.173 --> 04:00.806
And I guess they
called an ambulance.

04:00.941 --> 04:01.873
Bethany:
<i> An ambulance?</i>

04:02.009 --> 04:03.875
So you must've been
hurt pretty badly?

04:03.877 --> 04:05.577
My leg was broken
in three places

04:05.712 --> 04:07.379
And I suffered
a concussion.

04:07.381 --> 04:08.513
<i> I'm a cpa.</i>

04:08.549 --> 04:10.949
<i>I've had trouble focusing</i>
<i>since what happened.</i>

04:10.951 --> 04:12.484
Get headaches.

04:14.054 --> 04:16.588
I haven't been able
to go back to work.

04:16.590 --> 04:17.856
How long have you
been off work?

04:17.991 --> 04:19.324
Almost 13 months.

04:20.327 --> 04:21.893
Do you have a sense
from your doctor

04:21.895 --> 04:23.528
When you'll be
able to go back?

04:24.598 --> 04:26.698
They don't know
if I'll be able
to go back.

04:30.237 --> 04:34.639
(gentle music)

04:34.642 --> 04:37.509
Joyce:
<i> So you heard that gregor's</i>
<i> stepping down as chair?</i>

04:37.511 --> 04:39.144
I'll believe
that when I
see it.

04:39.213 --> 04:40.245
Joyce:
<i> Gregor's gone.</i>

04:40.314 --> 04:41.913
He's not even
in the country.

04:41.949 --> 04:43.949
He handed me his
proxy just in case.

04:44.084 --> 04:45.450
Still playing the
puppet master.

04:45.585 --> 04:47.051
Unbelievable.

04:47.855 --> 04:48.987
So who's gonna
replace him?

04:49.923 --> 04:51.790
Well, there's
eugene alfreds,

04:51.859 --> 04:53.258
Quinta tyson,

04:53.327 --> 04:54.259
Percy lincoln.

04:54.328 --> 04:56.261
Percy lincoln?
Seriously?

04:56.263 --> 04:57.395
Joyce:
<i> I wouldn't sweat it.</i>

04:57.531 --> 04:58.864
He's viewed as
too radical.

04:58.866 --> 05:00.631
Even the "left"
has its limits.

05:01.869 --> 05:03.634
Thinking about tossing
your hat in the ring?

05:04.404 --> 05:05.804
Give your head
a shake.

05:05.873 --> 05:07.339
You know how long I've
been trying to reform

05:07.408 --> 05:08.639
Halifax legal aid?

05:09.576 --> 05:11.810
Well, it sounds like
you have ideas.

05:11.879 --> 05:14.612
And the added bonus
is you have history,

05:14.648 --> 05:16.214
Aka you're old.

05:16.350 --> 05:17.849
Thanks, colleen.

05:20.654 --> 05:21.886
I'll think
about it.

05:27.661 --> 05:29.294
Ronnie:
<i> There the big</i>
<i> talking man is.</i>

05:29.296 --> 05:32.030
With your cheap
settler promises.

05:32.099 --> 05:33.698
I thought you were gonna
do something for us.

05:33.767 --> 05:35.533
<i>Now, I'm just</i>
<i>getting this.</i>

05:37.471 --> 05:39.838
We waited five months
for a no?

05:39.907 --> 05:42.907
The government's not
getting their hands
on my niece's kid.

05:42.943 --> 05:43.842
Hey.

05:43.977 --> 05:44.876
Hey, colleen.

05:45.011 --> 05:46.578
<i> You got a minute to</i>
<i> talk about this?</i>

05:46.713 --> 05:48.513
You the boss?

05:48.515 --> 05:49.681
I am, yeah.
How can I help?

05:49.750 --> 05:52.517
Stop screwing us with
your "nos" for a start.

05:52.519 --> 05:53.685
We rejected her claim.

05:54.788 --> 05:56.454
Okay, well you can
always appeal.

05:59.960 --> 06:01.325
Ronnie:
<i> Damn it!</i>

06:04.731 --> 06:06.330
My niece is 16.

06:06.367 --> 06:07.599
She's in the system.

06:07.601 --> 06:10.202
<i> Me and her mother,</i>
<i> we grew up in the system.</i>

06:10.337 --> 06:13.071
After my sister died,
I swore I wouldn't let ivy,

06:14.842 --> 06:17.075
She wasn't supposed to
end up in foster care.

06:18.545 --> 06:19.811
I let her down.

06:20.947 --> 06:23.648
How many more of us
do they get to claim?

06:23.717 --> 06:25.650
<i> That child of hers</i>
<i> belongs with her people.</i>

06:25.786 --> 06:27.652
I need to bring her home.

06:29.723 --> 06:31.489
Here, I want you to
write down your number.

06:31.525 --> 06:33.491
I'll call you this afternoon,
I promise.

06:38.432 --> 06:39.631
(door knocking)

06:39.700 --> 06:42.367
Doug:
<i> Look, I know you said</i>
<i> "no" but this file-</i>

06:42.369 --> 06:44.369
(sighs) there's
always a "file" doug.

06:44.371 --> 06:46.304
We don't have the resources
to take on every case.

06:46.373 --> 06:47.773
It's six or seven hours,
colleen.

06:47.908 --> 06:49.107
<i> Ronnie's niece is</i>
<i> in foster care.</i>

06:49.242 --> 06:51.910
<i> She's 16 and</i>
<i> eight months pregnant.</i>

06:51.912 --> 06:53.177
Ronnie just wants to
be appointed guardian

06:53.213 --> 06:54.179
Of her grand-nephew,

06:54.248 --> 06:55.213
Keep the child
out of care.

06:55.282 --> 06:56.647
<i> It's six or seven hours.</i>

06:57.718 --> 06:59.651
If she registers an
appeal I'll expedite it.

06:59.720 --> 07:01.486
You're not getting this,
colleen.

07:01.522 --> 07:02.821
<i> I'm sorry for taking</i>
<i> this out on you,</i>

07:02.956 --> 07:05.523
But she applied for legal
aid nearly five months ago.

07:05.592 --> 07:06.925
<i> We should be embarrassed</i>
<i> it takes this long</i>

07:06.927 --> 07:08.159
To respond to people.

07:08.195 --> 07:10.528
Wow, that's what
passes as an apology?

07:10.564 --> 07:12.597
Why does this woman
have to fight for help?

07:12.732 --> 07:14.332
We'll give a legal aid
certificate to a murderer

07:14.468 --> 07:16.000
Just like that.

07:16.036 --> 07:17.869
We have to be better.

07:17.871 --> 07:20.705
You have no idea what
I deal with on the daily.

07:20.741 --> 07:22.006
<i> Do more with less,</i>

07:22.042 --> 07:23.542
<i> Take from "peter"</i>
<i> to pay "paul".</i>

07:23.544 --> 07:26.077
The focus this quarter
is women not men,

07:26.079 --> 07:26.978
Black not white.

07:27.113 --> 07:29.481
Agendas are
constantly shifting.

07:29.616 --> 07:32.684
And every time I ask for more
I'm told to make it work.

07:32.819 --> 07:36.087
<i> And that's exactly what</i>
<i> I'm doing every day.</i>

07:36.089 --> 07:37.489
So don't,

07:37.491 --> 07:39.457
Don't come at me
suggesting otherwise.

07:40.761 --> 07:41.960
You're right.

07:41.962 --> 07:43.695
I shouldn't have said that,
I'm just...

07:46.433 --> 07:47.632
Ten hours, doug.

07:47.668 --> 07:49.233
I'll give you ten hours
to work this out.

07:49.269 --> 07:50.168
Thank you.

07:50.303 --> 07:51.235
Thank you, colleen.

07:51.271 --> 07:52.370
Colleen:
<i> And don't get too excited,</i>

07:52.372 --> 07:53.972
I'm not sanctioning court
time on this, all right?

07:53.974 --> 07:55.640
Couple of phone calls,
some meetings,

07:55.709 --> 07:57.442
Keep this really
short and simple.

08:00.214 --> 08:03.248
Bethany:
<i> Why did you choose</i>
<i> oakland park for your mom?</i>

08:03.250 --> 08:04.615
It seemed nice.

08:06.319 --> 08:07.319
I thought they'd take
good care of her,

08:07.454 --> 08:08.719
That she'd be safe.

08:08.755 --> 08:10.322
And was that the case?

08:10.457 --> 08:12.724
Uh, for the first
couple months.

08:12.793 --> 08:15.327
But then once she,
the accused,

08:15.462 --> 08:18.530
Um, became my mom's
continuing care assistant,

08:18.665 --> 08:22.000
It's like everything
just went to hell.

08:22.002 --> 08:25.003
I'd show up and mom would
be sitting in her own mess

08:25.005 --> 08:27.272
Or she'd need
an extra pillow

08:27.274 --> 08:29.407
And nina would look at
me like I had two heads.

08:29.443 --> 08:30.375
Hearsay.

08:30.444 --> 08:31.876
Judge kilcoyne:
<i> Move along, ms. Mayle.</i>

08:31.945 --> 08:34.078
Bethany:
<i> Did you speak to anyone</i>
<i> about your mom's care?</i>

08:34.114 --> 08:36.114
Eilidh:
<i> Not at first but</i>
<i> once she pushed me-</i>

08:36.183 --> 08:37.415
Objection, your honour.

08:37.417 --> 08:39.951
Bethany:
<i> It is our intention</i>
<i> to present evidence</i>

08:39.987 --> 08:41.419
Of a prior altercation

08:41.555 --> 08:43.487
Between ms. Macaskill
and the accused.

08:43.524 --> 08:44.522
Hmm.

08:44.525 --> 08:46.324
The witness can continue.

08:46.360 --> 08:47.993
She's lying.
I never touched her.

08:47.995 --> 08:50.161
I know. Nina, we're
gonna get our turn.

08:50.163 --> 08:52.163
Eilidh:
<i> Once that woman</i>
<i> pushed me,</i>

08:52.165 --> 08:53.365
<i> I complained to her boss</i>

08:53.367 --> 08:56.134
And the accused was taken
off my mother's care.

08:56.136 --> 08:58.570
So that was the end of
the defendant's interaction

08:58.639 --> 08:59.638
With your mother?

08:59.640 --> 09:02.373
No. As a result of covid,

09:02.442 --> 09:03.775
Oakland park was
short staffed

09:03.844 --> 09:06.978
So the accused was put
back on my mom's team.

09:06.980 --> 09:09.247
Bethany:
<i> How did your mother</i>
<i> respond to that?</i>

09:09.316 --> 09:10.382
Eilidh:
<i> I don't know.</i>

09:10.517 --> 09:12.650
Oakland park was
on lockdown.

09:12.786 --> 09:14.052
I didn't get to see her.

09:17.857 --> 09:19.290
My mother died
of covid.

09:21.862 --> 09:23.795
That woman gave
her covid-19-

09:23.930 --> 09:26.130
Objection! This is
highly prejudicial.

09:26.132 --> 09:28.266
Bethany:
<i> I'm as surprised</i>
<i> as ms. Diggs</i>

09:28.268 --> 09:29.834
To hear this
from my witness.

09:29.903 --> 09:31.870
However, we intend
to call evidence-

09:31.872 --> 09:34.339
And I will consider the
relevance of that evidence

09:34.341 --> 09:35.607
When it's put
before the court.

09:35.609 --> 09:37.142
Marcie:
<i> Your honour, the</i>
<i> complainant's allegations</i>

09:37.277 --> 09:38.809
Are entirely without basis.

09:38.845 --> 09:40.144
The jury needs
to be cautioned.

09:40.213 --> 09:42.313
She's a "hotspotter".

09:42.349 --> 09:43.281
<i> From preston.</i>

09:43.416 --> 09:44.716
<i> Even the</i>
<i> government said</i>

09:44.785 --> 09:46.884
<i> That that community was</i>
<i> a hotspot for covid.</i>

09:47.020 --> 09:47.918
Seriously, your honour.

09:47.955 --> 09:49.220
Judge kilcoyne:
<i> Ms. Macaskill,</i>

09:49.222 --> 09:51.055
<i> I need you to simply</i>
<i> answer the questions</i>

09:51.124 --> 09:53.024
Ms. Mayle asks of you.

09:53.093 --> 09:54.359
Don't editorialize,

09:54.428 --> 09:57.629
Don't present facts you
don't know as facts.

09:57.764 --> 09:59.631
<i> Ms. Diggs, I will take</i>
<i> your request for a caution</i>

09:59.766 --> 10:01.232
To the jury
under advisement.

10:02.402 --> 10:03.567
<i> Let's move this along.</i>

10:03.604 --> 10:05.303
Bethany:
<i> Let's go back</i>
<i> to the day</i>

10:05.305 --> 10:09.174
That the accused's vehicle
made contact with you.

10:09.309 --> 10:11.576
Did you have a
weapon in your hand

10:11.578 --> 10:13.111
<i> When you approached</i>
<i> the defendant?</i>

10:13.113 --> 10:14.445
No.

10:14.514 --> 10:16.848
Bethany:
<i> Were you planning to</i>
<i> physically harm the defendant?</i>

10:16.983 --> 10:18.383
I was upset,

10:18.452 --> 10:20.251
But I just wanted
to talk to her,

10:20.287 --> 10:22.253
To understand what
happened to my mother.

10:22.322 --> 10:23.754
I wasn't going
to hurt her.

10:24.558 --> 10:26.590
I have no
further questions.

10:26.592 --> 10:28.492
Judge kilcoyne:
<i> Ms. Diggs, cross.</i>

10:31.898 --> 10:33.264
Marcie:
<i> Your mother died.</i>

10:34.134 --> 10:35.467
This is someone
you idolized,

10:35.469 --> 10:37.402
Someone you loved.

10:37.471 --> 10:40.405
<i> And you blame nina francis</i>
<i> for her death?</i>

10:40.474 --> 10:42.440
Yes. Yes I do.

10:42.476 --> 10:45.043
Marcie:
<i> And, when you confronted</i>
<i> her at her home</i>

10:45.979 --> 10:47.511
You were angry.

10:47.547 --> 10:49.080
I wouldn't say angry, no.

10:49.215 --> 10:50.215
Marcie:
<i> No?</i>

10:50.217 --> 10:51.683
<i> Just thirty minutes before</i>

10:51.685 --> 10:55.153
<i> You were asking staff members</i>
<i> for my client's home address.</i>

10:55.222 --> 10:56.888
I wanted to talk
to her, yes. But-

